topic.title: Global Event Region

body.p: This region in the Global Address Space (GAS) comprises of the switch global event registers and a partition event bitmap register. These registers can show which partition has run into a partition event or port event. They also help to query partition events in the partition configuration region and port events in PCIe function CSR region.

body.p: Bit 2:49 - Partition 0-47, (RW, reserved for those invalid partitions)
bit[63,62] = b'10 : submit a request to clear all events
bit[63,62] = b'01 : the above request is done, and all events have been cleared.
A bit set means that there is partition event or port event in that partition
A bit set means there is event in corresponding event slot.
Bit 0 - Event Status. 0 - No event; 1 - Event happened, (RW1C)

Bit 4 - Fatal Error Event, make firmware stop running.
Bit 5:12 - Event occurring times since this event is cleared last time, (RO)
